```javascript
const toggle = document.querySelector('.nav-toggle');
const links = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
if (toggle && links) {
  toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
    links.classList.toggle('show');
  });
}
```

However, in about.html and other pages, they only load the external script.js file which has a `toggleMobileMenu()` function that toggled the 'active' class (not 'show'), and the event listener is never attached.

So the issue is:
1. The toggle event listener code is only in the index.html inline script
2. Other pages like about.html don't have this inline code
3. They only load script.js which has a toggleMobileMenu() function but doesn't attach any event listener

This is definitely an easy fix! The solution would be to:
1. Move the navigation toggle code from index.html's inline script into script.js
2. Make sure the class name matches between the JavaScript and CSS (it should be 'show')
3. Execute this code on DOMContentLoaded to ensure the DOM is ready

